An Act establishing the hunger-free campus initiative.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 15A of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
2 Section 48. (a) Subject to appropriation, there shall be a hunger-free campus grant
3 program managed by the department to provide grants to institutions of public higher education
4 to address student food insecurity and hunger. This grant program shall also be available to
5 municipally administered colleges and to minority-serving institutions as defined under 20
6 U.S.C. 1067k (3) as determined by the United States Department of Education. Funding for the
7 grant program may include, but not be limited to, appropriations from the Education and
8 Transportation Fund established in section 2BBBBBB of chapter 29.
9 Using funding allocated under the grant program, the department is authorized to hire a
10 director of the program who shall report to the commissioner. The director shall develop
11 guidelines and procedures governing the grant making process and the program using available
12 data pertaining to student hunger. The director may also conduct any additional surveys the
1 of 4

13 department deems necessary to understand gaps in addressing student food insecurity and hunger
14 eligible higher education campuses across the commonwealth.
15 The guidelines and procedures that govern the program shall specify any requirements
16 applicable to eligible institutions of higher education in order to apply and qualify for grants
17 under the program, including, but not limited to: (i) whether the institution has designated
18 campus staff to interface with the department; (ii) the existence and extent of any campus-level
19 hunger awareness programs, including notification to students of their rights to participate in
20 federal and state food assistance programs; (iii) whether the institution has established on-
21 campus meal vendors to accept available federal and state nutrition benefits; (iv) the existence or
22 development of a student meal credit sharing program; (v) income based standards by which
23 grant levels are determined according to the student population at each participating campus; and
24 (vi) any other pertinent criteria as developed by the department. The department shall further
25 develop and deliver technical assistance to assist eligible institutions of higher education to meet
26 the goals of this program.
27 (b) Subject to appropriation, the department shall award grants to institutions that have
28 met the guidelines and procedures established by the department and have submitted an
29 application to the department for a grant under this program. The department shall prioritize
30 regional equity and equitable distribution among types of institutions of public higher education
31 including the university of Massachusetts segment, the state university segment and the
32 community college segment in its distribution of grants. Upon recommendation by the director of
33 the program, the commissioner or a designee shall determine the amount of each grant which
34 shall be used by the institution to address food insecurity among its students in accordance with
35 the program and shall establish reporting guidelines for grant recipients.
