36 (c) Annually, not later than July 1, the department shall submit a report on the hunger-
37 free campus grant program for the preceding fiscal year to the governor, the clerks of the senate
38 and house of representatives and the joint committee on higher education. The report shall
39 include the number and amounts of grants to eligible institutions well as a comprehensive
40 assessment of the program for the applicable year, including, but not limited to: (i) identifying
41 the institutions participating in the program; (ii) describing the activities supported by awards;
42 (iii) describing the level of student engagement in activities; (iv) describing and analysing the
43 outcomes resulting from activities, including, but not limited to, the impact of the program in
44 reducing the number of students experiencing food insecurity; and (v) recommendations on any
45 changes to the program.
46 (d) There shall be established and set up on the books of the commonwealth a separate
47 fund to be known as the Hunger-Free Campus Trust Fund administered by the commissioner of
48 higher education. The fund shall be credited with: (i) revenue from appropriations or other
49 money authorized by the general court and specifically designated to be credited to the fund; (ii)
50 interest earned on such revenues; and (iii) funds from public and private sources such as gifts,
51 grants and donations. Amounts credited to the fund shall not be subject to further appropriation
52 and any money remaining in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall not revert to the General
53 Fund.
54 (e) Amounts credited to the fund shall be used to fund grants made pursuant to the
55 hunger-free campus grant program, and for the cost of administration of such program by the
56 department of higher education.
3 of 4

57 (f) Amounts received from private sources shall be approved by the commissioner of
58 higher education and subject to review before being deposited in the fund to ensure that pledged
59 funds are not accompanied by conditions, explicit or implicit, on the implementation of the
60 hunger-free campus grant program that may be detrimental to the program. The review shall be
61 made publicly available.
62 (g) Annually, not later than October 1, the commissioner shall report to the clerks of the
63 senate and house of representatives, the joint committee on higher education and the house and
64 senate committees on ways and means on the fund's activity including: (i) the source and amount
65 of funds received; (ii) the amounts distributed and the purpose of expenditures from the fund;
66 (iii) any grants provided to institutions of higher education and other stakeholder organizations;
67 and (iv) anticipated revenue and expenditure projections for the next year.
